Subject: Re: [T2] diff. in 6 pin Air Flow Meters- what year is this?

At 10:58 PM 10/1/02 -0400, Michael Benthin (MUTS) wrote:
>After a fatal backfire in the 75 bus (FI- bent the AFM flapper and even
>cracked the edge of the square casting) I checked my spare 6 pin AFM's-
>the one I used has the same 012 part number ending, and has a bolt
>sticking out the center of the meter flapper. It has 2 lines to the
>airbox, related to the charcoal canister and the breather box.  I have
>another 6 pin AFM which has an extra small tube connected to it, and the
>flapper has no bolt in the center.  It has the same part number, but the
>last digits are 006- what year is this from and should it work in the
>75?????
******************************
The 0280 200 006 AFM fits 77-79 Beetle Sedans and Convertibles, definitely
not a Type 2.

The 0280 200 012 is only for the 1975 Bus

Hope this helps :-)


